# ReconForge

### AI-assisted reconnaissance and security posture reporting for modern web applications.

![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-black)
![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.11%2B-blue)
![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/status-runnable_v1-success)
![Scope](https://img.shields.io/badge/scope-passive_recon-informational)

</div>

ReconForge is a polished, portfolio-ready security research project that discovers target metadata, evaluates basic security posture signals, and exports structured reports. It is designed to feel like a serious engineering system rather than a loose collection of scripts.

## Why ReconForge

- Clean CLI for discovery and scan workflows
- Passive by default and safer to demonstrate publicly
- JSON and Markdown report generation
- Docker-ready local execution
- Tests, CI, and architectural decision records included
- Strong README structure and research-lab style presentation

## System Architecture

```text
Target
  |
  v
HTTP Collector
  |
  +--> Discovery Engine ----> Metadata Profile
  |
  +--> Scan Engine ---------> Security Posture Findings
  |
  v
Report Renderer -----------> JSON / Markdown Output
```

## Features

- **Target discovery**: collects status, title, content type, server information, and same-origin links.
- **Technology hints**: infers likely frameworks from lightweight fingerprints.
- **Security posture checks**: identifies missing defensive headers and common information disclosure signals.
- **Report export**: saves structured findings to JSON and Markdown.
- **Developer-ready packaging**: installable package, Dockerfile, test suite, and GitHub Actions workflow.

## Quick Start

### Local install

```bash
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -e .[dev]
```

### Discover a target

```bash
reconforge discover https://example.com --json-out reports/discovery.json
```

### Run a scan

```bash
reconforge scan https://example.com --json-out reports/findings.json --md-out reports/findings.md
```

## Docker

```bash
docker build -t reconforge .
docker run --rm reconforge scan https://example.com
```

## Example Output

```json
{
  "target": "https://example.com",
  "final_url": "https://example.com",
  "status_code": 200,
  "findings": [
    {
      "severity": "medium",
      "title": "Missing Content-Security-Policy header",
      "details": "The response for https://example.com did not include Content-Security-Policy."
    }
  ]
}
```

